ng food and medicines.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michal Burda |url=https://zlinsky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pomoc-nejohrozenejsim-seniorum-privezou-nakupy-az-domu-20200318.html |title=Pomoc nejohro\u017een\u011bj\u0161\u00edm: senior\u016fm p\u0159ivezou n\u00e1kupy a\u017e dom\u016f \u2013 Zl\u00ednsk\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Zlinsky.denik.cz |date=18 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On Monday, 23 March, [[Czech Television|Czech National Television]] launched a temporary new television channel \u010cT3, which is to bring practical advice, news and a selection of \u010cT's classic programmes from the archive for older people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskatelevize.cz/porady/10000000408-naladte-se-na-ct3/ |title=Nala\u010fte se na \u010cT3 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The Vietnamese community in the [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]] region raised CZK 140,000 for a donation of a ventilator to a hospital in \u00dast\u00ed nad Labem<ref>{{cite web|author=Janni Vorl\u00ed\u010dek |url=https://ustecky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/vietnamska-komunita-se-slozila-na-plicni-ventilatory-pro-usteckou-nemocnici-20200323.html |title=Vietnamsk\u00e1 komunita se slo\u017eila na plicn\u00ed ventil\u00e1tory pro \u00fasteckou nemocnici \u2013 \u00dasteck\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Ustecky.denik.cz |date=23 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Due to the closure of Czech schools, Czech National Television launched an educational programme for home education. The \"U\u010d\u00edTelka\" programme is focusing on teaching first-grade pupils. The programmes \"Odpoledka\" on teaching second-grade pupils and programme \"\u0160kola doma\" for ninth grade pupils preparing them for entrance exams to secondary schools.<ref>{{cite web|author=16. 3. 2020, 10:52Jana Perglov\u00e1<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/ceska-televize-zacina-ucit-deti-zakladnich-skol-40316814 |title=\u010cesk\u00e1 televise za\u010d\u00edn\u00e1 u\u010dit d\u011bti z\u00e1kladn\u00edch \u0161kol |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Czech manufacturer of 3D printers [[Prusa Research]] contributed to the \"free use project\" of shared Bicycles company [[Rekola]] to enable access to transport with a lower risk of virus transmission than public transport.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/prusa-research-a-boj-s-koronavirem-jak-je-dulezite-byt-pripraven/ |title=Prusa Research a boj s koronavirem: jak je d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 b\u00fdt p\u0159ipraven \u2013 Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date=19 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> Prusa Research also designed, produced and distributed protective face shields for medical professionals.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/od-navrhu-k-hromadnemu-3d-tisku-zdravotnickych-stitu-behem-tri-dnu/ |title=Aktualizov\u00e1no 30.3. \u2013 Od n\u00e1vrhu k hromadn\u00e9mu 3D tisku zdravotnick\u00fdch \u0161t\u00edt\u016f b\u011bhem t\u0159\u00ed dn\u016f |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The \u017duf\u00e1nek family distillery from [[Bor\u0161ice]] will produce and distribute for free disinfectant gels without the necessary permit from the health and agriculture department.<ref>{{cite web | title=Zak\u00e1zali mi vyr\u00e1b\u011bt dezinfekci, st\u011b\u017euje si \u017duf\u00e1nek. O povolen\u00ed nest\u00e1l, \u0159\u00edkaj\u00ed celn\u00edci | website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz \u2013 V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje | date=23 March 2020 | url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/ekonomika/zufanek-dezinfekce/r~84235f126d0611ea80e60cc47ab5f122/ | language=cs | access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Let\u00e1k_MZCR_Coronavirus_A5.pdf|Information flyer from the Ministry of Health sent to every house address \nFile:Usnesen\u00ed vl\u00e1dy k vyhl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu.pdf|Government Resolution on Declaration of Emergency\nFile:COVID-19_Czech_Government_SMS_notification_about_shop_shutdown.jpg|SMS notification of the closure of shops\nFile:Celetn\u00e1 ulice bez turist\u016f 2020 03 203.jpg|Prague, Celetn\u00e1 ulice, without tourists(March 2020)\nFile:Starom\u011bstsk\u00fd orloj bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|Prague, Astronomical clock, without spectators (March 2020)\nFile:V\u00e1clavsk\u00e9 n\u00e1m\u011bst\u00ed bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|thumb|Prague, Wenceslas Square, without tourists (March 2020)\nFile:Praha Flora karant\u00e9na b\u0159ezen 2020.jpg|Prague, Flora shopping centre (March 2020)\nFile:No entry to driver's area in Brno city transport due to COVID-19 (detail).jpg|Brno, forbidden to enter front section of local bus. (March 2020)\nFile:Westfield Chodov NCOV-19.jpg|Empty shopping mall in the Czech Republic during COVID-19 pandemic\nFile:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|Interior of a Czech bus during COVID-19 pandemic (14 March 2020)\nFile:Antonov Airlines Antonov An-124-100 Vanzura-2.jpg|Antonov An-124-100 similar aeroplanetype which provided medical products purchased by the Czech government in China\nFile:Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9, drive-trhu COVID-19 testing.jpg|Drive thru testing centre at the University Hospital Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Healthcare in the Czech Republic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19/ Actual Situation Dashboard Ministry of healthcare]\n* [https://www.datawrapper.de/_/Sgf7v/ Epidemic curve from countries including the Czech Republic]\n* [https://covid-19-cz.chcepe.now.sh/ Interactive map of COVID-19 situation in the Czech Republic]\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://theenewstimes.com/corona-virus-live-statistics/ Live Statistics of Corona-virus on the World Map]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable standard floatleft\" style=\"text-align:left;margin-top: 12px;\"\n|+\n!Information from the Ministry of Health of the Czech Republic \u2013 COVID-19\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-odberovych-center/ Hospitals with COVID-19 testfacility \u2013 Blue is with self-pay testfacility]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-laboratori/ List of laboratories testing on COVID-19 in Czech Republic]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/en/ Important-phone-numbers and links// Emergency contact numbers]\n|-\n! Most services are available 24h and seven days a week\n|}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Czech Republic|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Czech Republic|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Czechia per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by region\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Czech Republic]]\n| first_case      = Unknown\n| arrival_date    = 1 March 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days\n | month1 = 03\n | day1   = 1\n | year1  = 2020\n | month2 = \n | day2   = \n | year2  = }} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China\n| confirmed_cases = 6,654<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| recovery_cases  = 1,227<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| deaths          = 181<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] saw its first three confirmed cases in the [[Czech Republic]] on 1 March 2020. On 12 March, the government declared a [[state of emergency]], for the first time in the country's modern history for the area of the entire country. On 16 March, the country closed its borders, forbade the entry of foreigners and issued a nationwide curfew. While originally planned until 24 March, the measures were later extended until 1 April<ref name=\"apnews\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-republic-severely-limits-freedom-of-movement-in-order-to-slow-down-coronavirus-spread|title=Czech Republic goes into quarantine to slow down coronavirus spread|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> and then again until the end of State of Emergency<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /> which was extended by the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] until 30 April 2020.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.psp.cz/eknih/2017ps/stenprot/043schuz/s043037.htm#h8 |title=P\u010cR, PS 2017 , 43. sch\u016fze, \u010d\u00e1st 37 (7. 4. 2020) |publisher=Psp.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nCzech Republic started gradual easing of measures from 7 April 2020 onwards.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /><ref name=\"sports allowed\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |date= |publisher=Government of the United Kingdom |url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |date= |website=wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/The Czech Republic medical cases chart}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:80%; float:right; clear:right; margin:0 0 0.5em 1em;\"\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in the Czech Republic<ref name=\":0\"/>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Date\n! colspan=\"2\" | Confirmed\n! colspan=\"2\" | Recovered\n! colspan=\"2\" | Deaths\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Active<br / >cases\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Tested<br/>(Total)\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Detected<br/>ratio\n|-\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n|-\n! 28 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 193\n| \n|-\n! 29 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 200\n| \n|-\n! 1 March\n| 3 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 211\n| {{#expr:3/(211-200)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 2 March\n| 0 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 262\n| {{#expr:0/(262-211)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 3 March\n| 2 || 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 340\n| {{#expr:2/(340-262)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 4 March\n| 0 || 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 407\n| {{#expr:0/(407-340)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 5 March\n| 3 || 8\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 8\n| 483\n| {{#expr:3/(483-407)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 6 March\n| 11 || 19\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 19\n| 594\n| {{#expr:11/(594-483)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 7 March\n| 7 || 26\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 26\n| 787\n| {{#expr:7/(787-594)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 8 March\n| 6 || 32\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 32\n| 928\n| {{#expr:6/(928-787)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 9 March\n| 6 || 38\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 38\n| 1,193\n| {{#expr:6/(1193-928)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 10 March\n| 25 || 63\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 63\n| 1,358\n| {{#expr:25/(358-193)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 1