fare programmes compelled to work duty.'''}}\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Actual work of students subject to later call-up.\n\nAt the same time welfare providers are ordered to provide welfare to recipients whose life or health may be in jeopardy (providers cannot refuse provision of welfare).\n\nWelfare provision aimed at persons that are not self-sufficient (elderly, crippled, etc.).\n| Government Resolution No. 207/2020<ref name=\"welfare\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_207.pdf |title=Data |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Army deployed.'''\n| 14 April 2020\n| From 14 April onwards (indefinitely).\n| 360 soldiers deployed to support provision of welfare, especially within retirement homes. Place of deployment of particular units dependent on requests from regional governments.\n| Government Regulation No. 172/2020 Coll.<ref>https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38839</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=5 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Social and economical support measures'''\n| '''Trucks allowed to drive on Sundays'''\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 13 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| Generally, freight trucks are banned from driving on Sundays to ease weekend return traffic. This long-standing ban was lifted to mitigate possible freight disruptions stemming from other measures or general COVID-19 impact.\n| Government Resolution No. 205/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"trucks on sundays\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_205.pdf |title=Trucks on Sundays |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Income tax deadline extended\n\nDeadline for Income Tax submission moved by 3 months for natural persons (new date is 1 July)\n| 12 March 2020\n|\n|\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| Loans repayment delayed\n\nBanks will provide an option of delaying loan payments for people and small businesses affected by the coronavirus\n| 12 March 2020\n|\n|\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| Gun sales registration period waived. \n| 16 March 2020\n| From 16 March until end of the curfew\n| In general, purchased firearms must be physically presented to the police for registration within 10 days from the sale (see [[Gun laws in the Czech Republic]]). Firearm sales still possible when delivered directly to customers' homes.\n\nFirearm registrations deemed non-essential by the Ministry of Interior Explanatory Note, as part of the general suspension of non-essential visits to government offices. Gun licence holders instructed to merely inform police about a purchase by post or electronic communication and visit station for registration after the end of curfew.\n\nAlso, exams required for new firearm licences suspended. New permits to purchase B-category firearms issued only remotely (by post or electronic communication). \n| Ministry of Interior Explanatory Note No. MV- 49249-2/OBP-2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mvcr.cz/soubor/zajistovani-spravnich-cinnosti-v-oblasti-zbrani-v-dobe-nouzoveho-stavu.aspx |title=Zajistovani |publisher=mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Forestry short-term hiring \n| March 2020\n| 2020 forestry season\n| Public company {{Interlanguage link|Lesy \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky|cs|Lesy \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky}} which manages public forests started massive short-term hiring of people from professions affected by quarantine measures. Temporary workers take part in restoration of spruce forests that suffered large scale damage by bark beetle and drought in previous years. Wage of CZK 120 per hour (ca \u20ac5 per hour), contracts for maximum of 300 hours per person.\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=V\u010dera 14:56Stanislav Pt\u00e1\u010dn\u00edk<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/praci-v-lesich-nasly-stovky-brigadniku-40319850 |title=Pr\u00e1ci v les\u00edch na\u0161ly stovky brig\u00e1dn\u00edk\u016f |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Criminal sanctions\n| COVID-19 added to list of diseases the wilful spreading of which constitutes a felony. \n| 13 March 2020\n|\n| '''Up to 10 years imprisonment in case of criminal negligence.'''\n|Government Resolution No. 210/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"criminal sanctions\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_210.pdf |title=Aktualne |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=9 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Healthcare provision support measures'''\n| {{No|'''Drive-through testing'''}}\n| 14 March 2020\n|\n| \"Drive-through\" tents set up in front of designated hospitals around the country. Patients don't need to leave their cars to be tested.\n\nTesting is free for people with prescriptions by the health authorities. Prescriptions are granted remotely (phone and email) based on symptoms and travel history. People lacking prescriptions may pay for their own tests. Prices vary depending on the hospital from CZK 1,300\u20133,000 (\u20ac50\u2013120). Some drive-through locations do not offer paid testing due to capacity limitations (i.e. they test only those with a prescription).\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blesk.cz/clanek/zpravy-koronavirus/637593/zmatek-v-testovani-na-nakazu-covid-19-vysetreni-si-muzete-zaplatit-v-peti-laboratorich.html|title=Koronavirus: Laborato\u0159e, kter\u00e9 mohou testovat a kde si m\u016f\u017eete test zaplatit|website=Blesk}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''COVID-19-only hospitals'''\n| 15 March 2020\n|\n| Two hospitals, {{Interlanguage link|Na Homolce Hospital|cs|Nemocnice Na Homolce}} in the capital and largest city of Prague, {{Interlanguage link|St. Anna University Hospital|cs|Fakultn\u00ed nemocnice u sv. Anny v Brn\u011b}} in the second largest city of Brno, were designated to deal with COVID-19 only. Both cities have several other hospitals to take up the caseload of other conditions.\n\nMilitary [[Biosafety level|BSL-4 reserve hospital]] at Biological Defense Center in [[T\u011bchon\u00edn]] put into a state of readiness.\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| 28 March 2020\n|\n| After COVID-19 infection spread in at least seven retirement homes, several hundred beds were set aside for quarantine and treatment of elderly with mild symptoms at:\n* Na Bulovce hospital in Prague\n* Na Franti\u0161ku hospital in Prague\n* Health resort at [[L\u00e1zn\u011b Tou\u0161e\u0148]]\n* Non-emergency section of Military BSL-4 reserve hospital at Biological Defense Center in T\u011bchon\u00edn\n| Ministry of Health decision<ref>{{cite web|author=Adam Vojt\u011bch@adamvojtechano |url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/domovy-pro-seniory-vyhrazena-luzka-v-nemocnicich-techonin-seniori-karantena-adam_2003281300_vtk |title=Ministerstvo vy\u010dlen\u00ed v nemocnic\u00edch stovky l\u016f\u017eek pro naka\u017een\u00e9 seniory. Aktivuje i T\u011bchon\u00edn &#124; iROZHLAS \u2013 spolehliv\u00e9 zpr\u00e1vy |publisher=Irozhlas.cz |date=28 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Medicine students' work duty'''}}\n| 15 March 2020\n| From 16 March until the end of State of Emergency\n| 5th- and 6th-year students of General Medicine compelled to work duty, actual work subject to later call-up.\n\nLast-year students of nursing, paramedics, and several other related fields compelled to work duty, actual work subject to later call-up.\n| Government Resolution No. 220 published as No. 90/2020 Coll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://apps.odok.cz/attachment/-/down/IHOABMRE46CG |title=Data |publisher=apps.odok.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 404 published as No. 158/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n|-\n| Healthcare workers' holiday ban\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 24 March until the end of State of Emergency\n\n'''Revoked on 10 April 2020.'''\n| Healthcare workers banned from taking a holiday (time off).\n| Government Resolution No. 278 published as 125/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"23 March Resolutions\"/>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 403 published as No. 157/2020 Coll. (revocation)<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n|-\n| '''Remdesivir provisional approval'''\n| 17 March 2020\n| From 17 March for a period of 9 months\n| [[Remdesivir]], originally developed by [[Gilead Sciences]] for [[ebola]] treatment, was approved for experimental use for COVID19 patients in serious condition.\n| Ministry of Health Decision No. MZDR 12059/2020-3/OLZP<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40603&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20LP%20Remdesivir.pdf |title=Remdisivir |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Plaquenil prescription restrictions'''\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 23 March 8&nbsp;pm onwards (indefinitely)\n| [[Hydroxychloroquine]], sold under the brand name Plaquenil among others, is a medication used for the prevention and treatment of certain types of malaria. Plaquenil showed promise in some COVID-19 trials. Only doctors with selected specialisations can prescribe it under the measure.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-2/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40681&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20p%C5%99edepisov%C3%A1n%C3%AD%20l%C3%A9%C4%8Div%C3%A9ho%20p%C5%99%C3%ADpravku%20Plaquenil%2023.%203.%202020.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> (until 3 April)\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-3/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40852&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20p%C5%99edepisov%C3%A1n%C3%AD%20l%C3%A9%C4%8Div%C3%A9ho%20p%C5%99%C3%ADpravku%20Plaquenil.pdf |title=Info |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> (after 3 April)\n|-\n| '''Hydroxychloroquine-sulfaat teva provisional approval'''\n| 7 April 2020\n| From 7 April for period of 8 months\n| Provisional approval for COVID-19 treatment due to plaquenil shortage.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 13360/2020-3/OLZP<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40885&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20LP%20HYDROXYCHLOROQUINE-SULFAAT%20TEVA.pdf |title=HYDROXYCHLOROQUINE-SULFAAT |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-3/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/> (after 3 April)\n|-\n| '''Avigan provisional approval'''\n| 16 April 2020\n| \n| Japanese medicine that showed promise in innitial trials for COVID-19 trestment.\n\nProvisional approval of 10,000 tablets donated by Japan.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 16312/2020-1/OLZP<ref>http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40963&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Rozhodnut%C3%AD%20o%20do%C4%8Dasn%C3%A9m%20povolen%C3%AD%20neregistrovan%C3%A9ho%20hum%C3%A1nn%C3%ADho%20l%C3%A9%C4%8Div%C3%A9ho%20p%C5%99%C3%ADpravku%20Avigan.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Hospitalised patients' information database\n| 24 March 2020\n| From 24 March onwards (indefinitely)\n| Central database about COVID-19 hospitalised patients. Hospital providers ordered to:\n* insert data about the state of hospitalised COVID-19 patients daily\n* insert data about every new patient that gets either to serious condition, requires ventilator or ECMO within one hour\n* insert data about every patient whose state changes as regards serious condition, use of ventilator or ECMO within one hour\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12996/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40693&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1znam%20o%20hospitalizovan%C3%A9m%20pozitivn%C3%ADm%20n%C3%A1lezu%20v%20ISIN.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Interpersonal solidarity==\n[[File:Ochrann\u00e1 rou\u0161ka, n\u00e1vod.webm|right|thumb|Demonstration of making facemasks without sewing]]\n\nThe COVID-19 pandemic in the Czech Republic has created a wave of solidarity in a variety of areas, including:\n* Due to the lack of protective face-masks, volunteers sewed masks for other people and also shared instruction videos online.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor ave, kac zdroj: \u010cT24, Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed |url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/domaci/3063778-jak-si-vyrobit-nouzovou-rousku-bez-siti-socialni-site-radi-kus-latky-ministerstvo-i |title=Jak si vyrobit nouzovou rou\u0161ku bez \u0161it\u00ed? Soci\u00e1ln\u00ed s\u00edt\u011b rad\u00ed kus l\u00e1tky, ministerstvo i pap\u00edrov\u00fd kapesn\u00edk \u2014 \u010cT24 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ct24.ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Programmes were launched to help the most vulnerable groups and seniors, on a non-commercial basis, by buying food and medicines.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michal Burda |url=https://zlinsky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pomoc-nejohrozenejsim-seniorum-privezou-nakupy-az-domu-20200318.html |title=Pomoc nejohro\u017een\u011bj\u0161\u00edm: senior\u016fm p\u0159ivezou n\u00e1kupy a\u017e dom\u016f \u2013 Zl\u00ednsk\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Zlinsky.denik.cz |date=18 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On Monday, 23 March, [[Czech Television|Czech National Television]] launched a temporary new television channel \u010cT3, which is to bring practical advice, news and a selection of \u010cT's classic programmes from the archive for older people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskatelevize.cz/porady/10000000408-naladte-se-na-ct3/ |title=Nala\u010fte se na \u010cT3 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The Vietnamese community in the [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]] region raised CZK 140,000 for a donation of a ventilator to a hospital in \u00dast\u00ed nad Labem<ref>{{cite web|author=Janni Vorl\u00ed\u010dek |url=https://ustecky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/vietnamska-komunita-se-slozila-na-plicni-ventilatory-pro-usteckou-nemocnici-20200323.html |title=Vietnamsk\u00e1 komunita se slo\u017eila na plicn\u00ed ventil\u00e1tory pro \u00fasteckou nemocnici \u2013 \u00dasteck\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Ustecky.denik.cz |date=23 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Due to the closure of Czech schools, Czech National Television launched an educational programme for home education. The \"U\u010d\u00edTelka\" programme is focusing on teaching first-grade pupils. The programmes \"Odpoledka\" on teaching second-grade pupils and programme \"\u0160kola doma\" for ninth grade pupils preparing them for entrance exams to secondary schools.<ref>{{cite web|author=16. 3. 2020, 10:52Jana Perglov\u00e1<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/ceska-televize-zacina-ucit-deti-zakladnich-skol-40316814 |title=\u010cesk\u00e1 televise za\u010d\u00edn\u00e1 u\u010dit d\u011bti z\u00e1kladn\u00edch \u0161kol |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Czech manufacturer of 3D printers [[Prusa Research]] contributed to the \"free use project\" of shared Bicycles company [[Rekola]] to enable access to transport with a lower risk of virus transmission than public transport.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/prusa-research-a-boj-s-koronavirem-jak-je-dulezite-byt-pripraven/ |title=Prusa Research a boj s koronavirem: jak je d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 b\u00fdt p\u0159ipraven \u2013 Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date=19 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> Prusa Research also designed, produced and distributed protective face shields for medical professionals.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/od-navrhu-k-hromadnemu-3d-tisku-zdravotnickych-stitu-behem-tri-dnu/ |title=Aktualizov\u00e1no 30.3. \u2013 Od n\u00e1vrhu k hromadn\u00e9mu 3D tisku zdravotnick\u00fdch \u0161t\u00edt\u016f b\u011bhem t\u0159\u00ed dn\u016f |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The \u017duf\u00e1nek family distillery from [[Bor\u0161ice]] will produce and distribute for free disinfectant gels without the necessary permit from the health and agriculture department.<ref>{{cite web | title=Zak\u00e1zali mi vyr\u00e1b\u011bt dezinfekci, st\u011b\u017euje si \u017duf\u00e1nek. O povolen\u00ed nest\u00e1l, \u0159\u00edkaj\u00ed celn\u00edci | website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz \u2013 V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje | date=23 March 2020 | url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/ekonomika/zufanek-dezinfekce/r~84235f126d0611ea80e60cc47ab5f122/ | language=cs | access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Let\u00e1k_MZCR_Coronavirus_A5.pdf|Information flyer from the Ministry of Health sent to every house address \nFile:Usnesen\u00ed vl\u00e1dy k vyhl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu.pdf|Government Resolution on Declaration of Emergency\nFile:COVID-19_Czech_Government_SMS_notification_about_shop_shutdown.jpg|SMS notification of the closure of shops\nFile:Celetn\u00e1 ulice bez turist\u016f 2020 03 203.jpg|Prague, Celetn\u00e1 ulice, without tourists(March 2020)\nFile:Starom\u011bstsk\u00fd orloj bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|Prague, Astronomical clock, without spectators (March 2020)\nFile:V\u00e1clavsk\u00e9 n\u00e1m\u011bst\u00ed bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|thumb|Prague, Wenceslas Square, without tourists (March 2020)\nFile:Praha Flora karant\u00e9na b\u0159ezen 2020.jpg|Prague, Flora shopping centre (March 2020)\nFile:No entry to driver's area in Brno city transport due to COVID-19 (detail).jpg|Brno, forbidden to enter front section of local bus. (March 2020)\nFile:Westfield Chodov NCOV-19.jpg|Empty shopping mall in the Czech Republic during COVID-19 pandemic\nFile:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|Interior of a Czech bus during COVID-19 pandemic (14 March 2020)\nFile:Antonov Airlines Antonov An-124-100 Vanzura-2.jpg|Antonov An-124-100 similar aeroplanetype which provided medical products purchased by the Czech government in China\nFile:Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9, drive-trhu COVID-19 testing.jpg|Drive thru testing centre at the University Hospital Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Healthcare in the Czech Republic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19/ Actual Situation Dashboard Ministry of healthcare]\n* [https://www.datawrapper.de/_/Sgf7v/ Epidemic curve from countries including the Czech Republic]\n* [https://covid-19-cz.chcepe.now.sh/ Interactive map of COVID-19 situation in the Czech Republic]\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://theenewstimes.com/corona-virus-live-statistics/ Live Statistics of Corona-virus on the World Map]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable standard floatleft\" style=\"text-align:left;margin-top: 12px;\"\n|+\n!Information from the Ministry of Health of the Czech Republic \u2013 COVID-19\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-odberovych-center/ Hospitals with COVID-19 testfacility \u2013 Blue is with self-pay testfacility]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-laboratori/ List of laboratories testing on COVID-19 in Czech Republic]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/en/ Important-phone-numbers and links// Emergency contact numbers]\n|-\n! Most services are available 24h and seven days a week\n|}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Czech Republic|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coro