{"title_page": "Dafne Keen", "text_new": "{{short description|British-Spanish actress}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Spanish name|Keen|Fern\u00e1ndez}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Dafne Keen\n| image         = Dafne Keen by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption       = Dafne Keen at the 2019 [[San Diego Comic-Con]].\n| birth_name    = Dafne Mar\u00eda Keen Fern\u00e1ndez<ref>Debrett's Peerage and Baronetage, 148th edition, Debrett's Peerage Ltd, 2011, p. 799</ref>\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|2005|1|4}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BsVNZUdnIGj/|title=Dafne Keen on Instagram: \"Had the best 14th birthday ever on the 4th!!!! \ud83d\udda4 I couldn't post until now but it was AMAZING\"|website=Instagram|date=7 January 2019|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place   = [[Madrid]], Spain\n| citizenship   = {{flatlist|\n* Spanish\n* British}}\n| occupation    = Actress\n| years_active  = 2014\u2013present\n| parents       = {{ubl|[[Will Keen]]|Mar\u00eda Fern\u00e1ndez Ache}}\n| relatives     =\n}}\n\n'''Dafne Mar\u00eda Keen Fern\u00e1ndez''' (born 4 January 2005)<ref>Debrett's Peerage and Baronetage, 148th edition, Debrett's Peerage Ltd, 2011, p. 799</ref> is a British-Spanish actress.<ref name=\"Behind scenes\">{{cite news |title=His Dark Materials: Behind the scenes of the TV adaptation |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-50042989 |accessdate=15 October 2019 |agency=BBC}}</ref> She played the role of Ana \"Ani\" Cruz Oliver in the television series ''[[The Refugees (TV series)|The Refugees]]'', and the [[mutant (Marvel Comics)|mutant]] [[X-23|Laura Kinney / X-23]] in the 2017 film ''[[Logan (film)|Logan]]''. As of 2019 she plays [[Lyra Belacqua|Lyra Belacqua/Silvertongue]] in the BBC/HBO television series ''[[His Dark Materials (TV series)|His Dark Materials]]''. I hope I'll be married with her. Oleksii Tupitskiy \n\n== Life and career ==\n[[File:Dafne Keen Press Conference Logan Berlinale 2017 02.jpg|right|thumb|Keen at the 2017 [[Berlin Film Festival]]]]\nKeen was born in [[Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.fotogramas.es/noticias-cine/a18526976/dafne-keen-las-nuevas-garras-de-lobezno/ |title=DAFNE KEEN, LAS NUEVAS GARRAS DE LOBEZNO|newspaper=Fotogramas|language=es|date=24 April 2017|access-date=20 May 2019}}</ref> She is the daughter of British actor [[Will Keen]], and [[Galicians|Galician]] actress,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/sociedad/2017/05/11/hija-lobezno-gallega/0003_201705H11P68992.htm|title=La hija de Lobezno es gallega|newspaper=[[La Voz de Galicia]]|language=es|date=11 May 2017|access-date=20 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lavozdegalicia.es/noticia/ourense/verin/2018/09/28/actriz-verinense-dafne-keen-protagoniza-serie-cara-historia-bbc-britanica/0003_201809O28C8993.htm|title=La actriz verinense Dafne Keen protagoniza la serie m\u00e1s cara de la historia de la BBC brit\u00e1nica|newspaper=[[La Voz de Galicia]]|language=es|date=28 September 2018|access-date=20 May 2019}}</ref> theatre director and writer Mar\u00eda Fern\u00e1ndez Ache.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/logan-film/2017/feb/16/logans-dafne-keen-cutting-her-teeth-and-claws-on-the-big-screen-as-x-23 |title=Logan's Dafne Keen: cutting her teeth \u2013 and claws \u2013 on the big screen as X-23 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=16 February 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303202944/https://www.theguardian.com/logan-film/2017/feb/16/logans-dafne-keen-cutting-her-teeth-and-claws-on-the-big-screen-as-x-23 |archivedate=3 March 2017}}</ref> A paternal great-grandfather was [[Edward Curzon, 6th Earl Howe]];<ref>Burke's Peerage, Baronetage and Knightage, 107th edition, vol. 2, Burke's Peerage, Ltd, 2003, p. 1987</ref><ref>Debrett's Peerage and Baronetage, 148th edition, Debrett's Peerage Ltd, 2011, p. 799</ref> her aunts are poet [[Alice Oswald]] and writer [[Laura Beatty]].<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/3588888/Going-with-the-flow.html</ref><ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gardening/gardens-to-visit/the-world-of-mary-keen</ref>\n\nKeen made her acting debut in 2014 alongside her father in the television series ''[[The Refugees (TV series)|The Refugees]]'', where she played Ana \"Ani\" Cruz Oliver.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Levine|first1=Daniel S.|title=Dafne Keen as X-23: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2016/10/sienna-novikov-as-x-23-who-plays-in-logan-hugh-jackman-wolverine-men-trailer-is-laura-kinney-bio-marvel/|accessdate=24 October 2016|work=[[Heavy.com]]|date=20 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nKeen starred in the 2017 film ''[[Logan (film)|Logan]]'' as [[X-23|Laura]], the child clone of [[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]].<ref>{{cite news|title='Logan' Image Teases Dafne Keen as Mutant X-23|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/23/logan-wolverine-dafne-keen-x-23-laura-kinney|accessdate=24 October 2016|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=23 October 2016}}</ref> From 2019 she plays [[Lyra Belacqua]], the heroine of [[Philip Pullman]]\u2019s ''[[His Dark Materials]]'' trilogy, in the [[His Dark Materials (TV series)|television adaptation]].<ref name=\"Behind scenes\"/>\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Logan (film)|Logan]]''\n| [[X-23|Laura]]<!-- The actual end credits of the movie say \"Laura\" and that is all that belongs here. |date=June 2017 -->\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Ana''\n| Ana\n| \n|}\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[The Refugees (TV series)|The Refugees]]''\n| Ana \"Ani\" Cruz Oliver\n| Recurring role, 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[His Dark Materials (TV series)|His Dark Materials]]''\n| [[Lyra Belacqua|Lyra Belacqua / Silvertongue]]\n| Main role, 8 episodes\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominated wor